      "writtenOn": "2017-07-14T14:20:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Haha, yep. This is what you get when you don\u0027t try to implement/compile...\n\nBut I hope this gives you the gist of what I\u0027m thinking.\n\nThe one thing I\u0027m not sure about is what to do with the SkStream. In the other factories, I delete it on failure. This makes sense for Android, where they\u0027re not going to try to use it again. But it means you have to create a new one if there wasn\u0027t enough data. Yours is just a wrapper for your SegmentReader, but it seems friendlier to not delete it. On an actual failure, though, maybe I should delete it, since you\u0027re not going to use it?",
      "parentUuid": "827b6f48_ffc1ea74",
